from collections import Counter
n = int(input())
for _ in range(n):
    s = int(input())
    currSum = 0
    reversedList = []
    for digit in range(9, -1, -1):
        currSum += digit
        reversedList.append(digit)
        if currSum >= s:
            currSum -= digit
            reversedList.pop()
            break
    diff = s - currSum
    reversedList.append(diff)
    res = map(str, reversed(reversedList))
    print(''.join(res))

n_testcases = int(input())
results = []
while n_testcases > 0:
    max_usable = 9
    to_reach = int(input())
    num = []
    left = to_reach
    while left > 0 and max_usable > 0:
        while max_usable <= left and max_usable > 0:
            num.append(str(max_usable))
            left -= max_usable
            max_usable -= 1
        max_usable -= 1
    num_int = int(''.join(num[::-1]))
    results.append(num_int)
    n_testcases -= 1
for i in range(len(results)):
    print(results[i])
